    {
      "repo": "sg-benchmarks/expressjs-express",
      "path": "package.json",
      "version": "^0.7.1"
    }
  ],
  "text": "During a comprehensive security audit of the Node.js web stack, I searched all four repositories (nodejs/node, sg-benchmarks/expressjs-express, sg-benchmarks/lodash, and sg-benchmarks/prisma-prisma) for direct runtime dependencies on the 'cookie' npm package. The search focused specifically on entries in the 'dependencies' section of package.json files, excluding devDependencies and other dependency types. Only one match was found: the expressjs-express repository declares 'cookie' as a direct runtime dependency with version constraint '^0.7.1' in its root package.json file. The nodejs/node repository contains no cookie dependencies in any of its package.json files. The lodash repository has no 'dependencies' section at all, only devDependencies. The prisma-prisma repository contains only 'cookie-es' (a different package) in devDependencies, not the vulnerable 'cookie' package in runtime dependencies."
}

